Package gmbh.kdb.hsw.gdp

Class Game

java.lang.Object
gmbh.kdb.hsw.gdp.Game
public final class Game extends Object
A Game captures the state of an active game

Only one game can be active at a time. This class therefore provides a method to create a new game instance create(IGameHandler) as well as a method to retrieve the active instance (get()).

The pattern is to create a new game with a handler and then start it: 

 Game
      .create(game -> {

      })
      .run();

    • Game

      public Game​(IGameHandler handler, GameDevStudio studio)
      Creates a new game with the given handler and initial studio.

      If studio is not null, no random roll of properties will be performed. Otherwise, a random studio will be generated.

      Parameters:
      handler - Game round handler
      studio - Initial studio
